Authenticate to the Sentinel platform using email/password or an API token (not Kubernetes).

Use this for day-to-day deploy and registry-related flows. Cluster install and admin work
use Kubernetes and the cluster commands, not this command.

The token is stored in a local file (mode 0600) under the user config directory, unless you set MCP_PLATFORM_API_TOKEN.

Optional environment:
  MCP_PLATFORM_API_URL      default API base for login, e.g. https://platform.example.com
  MCP_PLATFORM_API_TOKEN    use this token for API calls; overrides a saved file
  MCP_RUNTIME_CONFIG_DIR    override the config directory (mainly for tests)

Usage:
  mcp-runtime auth [command]

Available Commands:
  login       Save a platform API token and optional registry host
  logout      Delete saved platform credentials on this machine
  status      Show whether platform API credentials are configured

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for auth

Global Flags:
      --debug   Enable debug mode with structured error logging

Use "mcp-runtime auth [command] --help" for more information about a command.
